# Command joplin

## What does this command do:

Joplin - privacy-focused note taking app with sync capabilities and stores as Markdown

## Installed from

For Fedora install using: NPM_CONFIG_PREFIX=~/.joplin-bin npm install --loglevel=error -g joplin && ln -sf ~/.joplin-bin/bin/joplin ~/.local/bin/joplin
For Raspberry Pi install using: NPM_CONFIG_PREFIX=~/.joplin-bin npm install --loglevel=error -g joplin && ln -sf ~/.joplin-bin/bin/joplin ~/.local/bin/joplin
For Mac install using: NPM_CONFIG_PREFIX=~/.joplin-bin npm install --loglevel=error -g joplin && ln -sf ~/.joplin-bin/bin/joplin ~/.local/bin/joplin

## Command path

For Fedora run: ~/.local/bin/joplin
For Raspberry Pi run: ~/.local/bin/joplin
For Mac run: ~/.local/bin/joplin

## Command documentation

Docs can be found at https://github.com/laurent22/joplin

## Command options

# Launch the TUI
joplin

# Show version
joplin version

# List notes in current notebook
joplin ls

# List notebooks
joplin ls -n

# Show note content
joplin cat <note>

# Show note with full metadata
joplin cat -v <note>

# Create a new notebook
joplin mkbook <notebook>

# Create a new note
joplin mknote <title>

# Create a new to-do
joplin mktodo <title>

# Switch to a notebook
joplin use <notebook>

# Edit a note (opens $EDITOR)
joplin edit <note>

# Move note to another notebook
joplin mv <note> <notebook>

# Rename a note or notebook
joplin ren <item> <name>

# Delete a note
joplin rmnote <note>

# Delete a notebook
joplin rmbook <notebook>

# Tag a note
joplin tag add <tag> <note>

# List tags
joplin tag ls

# Sync with configured target
joplin sync

# Configure sync target (e.g. 5=Nextcloud, 7=Dropbox, 10=Joplin Cloud)
joplin config sync.target <number>

# Show/set a config value
joplin config [name] [value]

# Show all config including hidden
joplin config -v

# Export notes (JEX format)
joplin export <path>

# Import notes
joplin import <path> [notebook]

# Attach a file to a note
joplin attach <note> <file>

# End-to-end encryption commands
joplin e2ee enable
joplin e2ee disable
joplin e2ee status
